title: Spring Hill Police K-9 officially retires after 'tirelessly' protecting community
text:
Spring Hill Police K-9 officially retires after ‘tirelessly’ protecting community
“Faith’s loyalty, dedication, and service will never be forgotten,” the police department said.
SPRING HILL, Tenn. (WSMV) - A Middle Tennessee Police K-9 is entering retirement after a career of “tirelessly” protecting the community.
“Faith,” the Spring Hill Police K-9, is retiring, and the department is celebrating her.
“Faith proudly served alongside her last handler, Officer York Walker, forming a strong and trusted team within the Spring Hill Police Department,” the police department said. “Together, they worked tirelessly to protect our community and support fellow officers. Faith’s loyalty, dedication, and service will never be forgotten.”
The police department thanked Faith for her dedicated service and wished her well in her retirement.
“Please join us in thanking K9 Faith and Officer Walker for their service and wishing Faith a long, happy, and well-deserved retirement filled with rest, play, and plenty of treats,” the police department said. “Thank you for everything, Faith—you’ve earned it!"
